	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="indent(2)">My dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have written this by the special request of the most respect<lb/>able members of the <placeName>Charleston</placeName> reformed Synagogue with the view if<lb/> possible to stop the&#44; so called&#44; progress some of their members are bent<lb/> on making which&#44; it is clear&#44; will ultimately lay Judaism prostrate<lb/> The promoters of this&#44; who are also your sincere friends&#44; trust that<lb/> you will give this an insertion at your earliest opportunity&#44; for<lb/> their sakes as well as for the sake of the upholding our Religion gen<lb/>erally&#44; and that you will not spare your own able pen in support<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> the principles advocated herein.  The <persName>Revd Mr Nathan</persName> of<placeName> N. O</placeName><lb/> <add>&#63;</add> kindly taken the trouble to copy it and has prepared this for <add>&#63;</add><lb/> with my alterations and additions thereto you can do as you please<lb/> <sic>Whereever</sic> I came I found your prospectus in the hands of your friends<lb/> who I am happy to inform you are very many <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>  I am now on my return to <placeName>New York</placeName> and hope to have the pleasure soon<lb/> to see you   Remaining my dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">yours faithfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">S. Newman</persName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>The <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>371 Walnut St.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
